## Project Description\
\
This project utilizes Terraform to provision a robust AWS environment suitable for hosting a web application. It includes a Virtual Private Cloud (VPC), EC2 instances in an Auto Scaling Group (ASG), a Relational Database Service (RDS) instance, S3 buckets, and comprehensive monitoring and logging.\
\
\
\
## Components\
\
-   **VPC (Virtual Private Cloud):**\
    -   Custom VPC with public and private subnets across two Availability Zones (AZs).\
    -   Internet Gateway (IGW) for public subnet access.\
    -   NAT Gateways in public subnets for private subnet internet access.\
    -   Route tables and subnet associations.\
-   **EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud):**\
    -   EC2 instances in an Auto Scaling Group (ASG) for scalability and high availability.\
    -   Application Load Balancer (ALB) to distribute traffic across EC2 instances.\
    -   Launch template for consistent EC2 configurations.\
-   **RDS (Relational Database Service):**\
    -   Managed MySQL database instance in private subnets.\
    -   Multi-AZ deployment for high availability.\
    -   AWS Secrets Manager for storing database credentials.\
-   **S3 (Simple Storage Service):**\
    -   General purpose S3 bucket for application data and static assets.\
    -   Dedicated S3 bucket for CloudTrail logs.\
    -   Versioning, server-side encryption (SSE-KMS), and lifecycle rules.\
    -   Public access blocked.\
-   **Monitoring and Logging:**\
    -   CloudWatch alarms for EC2 and RDS CPU utilization.\
    -   CloudTrail for audit logging.\
