## Usage\
\
After deployment:\
\
-   Access the web application through the ALB's DNS name.\
-   Database credentials are stored in AWS Secrets Manager (named `rds_credentials`).\
-   CloudWatch alarms and logs can be viewed in the AWS Management Console.\
\
## Security Considerations\
\
-   Security groups configured with the principle of least privilege.\
-   IAM roles used for EC2 instances and other AWS services.\
-   AWS Secrets Manager for sensitive data.\
-   S3 buckets with blocked public access and encryption.\
-   CloudTrail enabled for audit logging.\
-   RDS instance deployed in private subnets.\
\
## Monitoring and Logging\
\
-   CloudWatch alarms monitor EC2 and RDS CPU utilization.\
-   CloudTrail logs API calls to a dedicated S3 bucket.\
-   CloudWatch logs can be used for application logs (if configured).\
